Consider:

{foo}
   {bar:1}
   {bar:2}
   {bar:3}
{foo}

The {foo} macro needs to draw a header and footer based on the invocations of the {bar} macro. We need to ensure that the {bar} macros are always invoked first, and that the {foo} macro can access information left by them in the render context.

